---
title: Chorizo and Beef Chili Dinner with a Chili Burrito for Lunch
description: Cook it once, eat it twice: tonight’s dinner extras transform into tomorrow’s lunch. That’s thanks to special added ingredients that can easily be heated up, even at the office (your coworkers will be amazed, trust us). For the first meal in this 2-in-1 recipe, there’s a hearty beef and chorizo chili over rice with all the fixings. The next day, it rolls right into a burrito that tastes even better once the spices have had some time to rest. *The Lunch Burrito information is as follows: Calories: 660, Fat: 34 g, Saturated Fat: 17 g, Carbohydrate: 57 g, Sugar: 7 g, Fiber: 5 g, Protein: 30 g, Cholesterol: 100 mg, Sodium: 1240 mg. The nutrition facts panel below represents the nutrient values for the Chorizo and Beef Chili Dinner*
